title.narrative: Output 2.2: HEALTH ?By 2022, National capacity for quality assurance of primary and secondary maternal, neonatal, child andadolescent health (MNCHA) services is strengthened.?

description.narrative: Primary Health Care capacities were enhanced to deliver integrated quality Maternal and;Child;Health services through UNICEF interventions;including;capacity-building of health managers and service providers, improved infrastructure and engagement of communities.; In 2021, over 789,640 families were reached with health messages,;a total of 1,055,155 children and women received essential healthcare services;and133,250 live births took place in facilities supported by UNICEF. More than 2400 health providers were trained on MCH,;IMCI and use of social media. 62 PHC facilities were rehabilitated for WASH and;398,816 children in 360 primary schools have improved their WASH;practices.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:29/12/2021
